<div id="review_2425851386" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2425851386" />
    <a title="Czarny Pies" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/29160274-czarny-pies"><img alt="Czarny Pies" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1400687408p2/29160274.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2425851386?book_show_action=true">Jun 16, 2018</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Czarny Pies" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Czarny Pies" href="/user/show/29160274-czarny-pies">Czarny Pies</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>


          <div><span class="uitext greyText">Recommends it for: </span>
           <span class="uitext reviewText">This is a wonderful book for first year students in French Lit programs.</span></div>

        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/29160274-czarny-pies?shelf=french-lit">french-lit</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2425851386" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer3895035623730895824">This book has above all a superb pedagogical vocation; that is to say it is extremely useful for any introductory course of French literature given at an Anglophone university. It is clear and easy to read for the student who is not a native French speaker. First published in 1788, it provides a remarkable portrait of the state of mind of the French aristocracy on the eve of the Revolution. At the same time it contains a remarkable synthesis of the beliefs and doctrines of the Enlightenment phil</span>
  <span id="freeText3895035623730895824" style="display:none">This book has above all a superb pedagogical vocation; that is to say it is extremely useful for any introductory course of French literature given at an Anglophone university. It is clear and easy to read for the student who is not a native French speaker. First published in 1788, it provides a remarkable portrait of the state of mind of the French aristocracy on the eve of the Revolution. At the same time it contains a remarkable synthesis of the beliefs and doctrines of the Enlightenment philosophers. For a book that is short and quickly read it offers remarkable value.<br /><br />I hope that "Paul et Virginie" stays on the undergraduate program for French Lit majors at English-Speaking universities for a long time to come. There is really no other book that tells the Anglophone reader so much about the "Siècle des lumières" in such a brief lapse of time.</span>
  <a data-text-id="3895035623730895824" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


