<div id="review_3827034922" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3827034922" />
    <a title="Hunter" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/51460997-hunter"><img alt="Hunter" src="https://s.gr-assets.com/assets/nophoto/user/m_50x66-82093808bca726cb3249a493fbd3bd0f.png" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3827034922?book_show_action=true">Feb 18, 2021</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Hunter" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Hunter" href="/user/show/51460997-hunter">Hunter</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Hardcover 9780720605983" href="/book/show/14770709-paul-and-virginia">review of another edition</a>


        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3827034922" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer3801986201404628170">This is a tragic melodrama about two young lovers who grew up together on an island off the coast of Madagascar. Nature plays a central role in the telling of this story, and the author&apos;s experience as a botanist leads to elaborate nature descriptions. While there are many moments with really beautiful and captivating prose, there are also many moments where the prose is unnecessarily lengthy and laborious. I felt that there were times that the characters were overwrought with emotion. All in al</span>
  <span id="freeText3801986201404628170" style="display:none">This is a tragic melodrama about two young lovers who grew up together on an island off the coast of Madagascar. Nature plays a central role in the telling of this story, and the author's experience as a botanist leads to elaborate nature descriptions. While there are many moments with really beautiful and captivating prose, there are also many moments where the prose is unnecessarily lengthy and laborious. I felt that there were times that the characters were overwrought with emotion. All in all, this was a decent short work of fiction that I would recommend if you're interested in the romantic period of literature or French literature.</span>
  <a data-text-id="3801986201404628170" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
